Alias - Annotation Type in com.github.dm.jrt.object.annotation
This annotation allows to identify the method through a constant, thus avoiding issues when running obfuscation tools.
AsyncIn - Annotation Type in com.github.dm.jrt.object.annotation
Through this annotation it is possible to indicate the original parameter type of the target object method.
AsyncIn.InputMode - Enum in com.github.dm.jrt.object.annotation
Input transfer mode type.
The mode indicates in which way a parameter is passed to the wrapped method.
AsyncMethod - Annotation Type in com.github.dm.jrt.object.annotation
Through this annotation it is possible to indicate the original parameter types of the target object method, and the wrapping routine output mode.
AsyncOut - Annotation Type in com.github.dm.jrt.object.annotation
Through this annotation it is possible to indicate that the result returned by the target object method must be dispatched in an asynchronous way.
If, on the contrary, this annotation is missing, be aware that the proxy method will block until the target one completes, even if no result is expected (that is, the method returns a void result).
AsyncOut.OutputMode - Enum in com.github.dm.jrt.object.annotation
Output transfer mode type.
The mode indicates in which way the result is passed outside.

method(String) - Method in interface com.github.dm.jrt.object.builder.ObjectRoutineBuilder
Returns a routine used to call the method whose identifying name is specified in a Alias annotation.
If no method with the specified alias is found, this method will behave like ObjectRoutineBuilder.method(String, Class[]) with no parameter.
Optional com.github.dm.jrt.object.annotation.* method annotations will be honored as well.
Note that such annotations will override any configuration set through the builder.
